# dockerIf

A C API to interact with the Docker socket, abstracts some common uses cases for me

Slowly Adding


### Installing

A makefile is provided, so the usual steps of make and make install

```
make
make install
```
This will generate a static archive (.a) and install it in /usr/local/lib.

## Running the tests

No Tests yet


### How to use

Explain what these tests test and why

```
#include <cDocker.h>
//Define a context object
SocketContext ctx;

//Initialize
//          *ctx    Docker Version             Docker Socket     Hostname (docker.sock if NULL)
dockerIfInit(&ctx,      "v1.24",         "/var/run/docker.sock",           NULL                );



//Destroy context once done
cDockerDestroy(&ctx);
```

compile with the
```
-ldockerIf
```
flag


